race.comment: REGENERATION (7) resumes having run a good race on debut here when third and he has trialled well leading into this preparation for the Freedman yard. Looks ready to go to the next level this time in, though he won't need to have improved much to be winning. FORCEOFONE (3) resumes having been firmly in the market in the G3 Chairman's Stakes on debut, struggling there. Respecting that support in an easier race. RATHLIN EXPRESS (6) narrowly beat home REGENERATION when they met here on debut and was also sent for a spell. Kicks off here from a good gate and is right in this. WHISKEY JOE (8) is a Snitzel colt on debut for the Price & Kent Jnr yard who should run well.
